A burst of flames erupted from Thassalin's jaws as the colossal Thraki set a precise patch of the forest ablaze, then flew in circles above, observing it for a time. Bizarrely, as it had slowed, the strange sounds of cries behind it had stopped. Thassalin had forgotten that he had passengers on his back.
"Come on, Tenuk, you've already turned into a Thraki before!"
"My flight is very different. I don't let myself be lifted violently by a huge pink dragon!"
"It's not so unpleasant, is it, Kayel?"
Kayel was clearly not in agreement with Nyssi, he seemed less black than usual and had planted his claws in the back of Thassalin, to the point where he had made the Thraki bleed, but clearly, he didn't care. However, Thassalin had realized that he had terrorized his new friends and had found a clearing to land.
"My apologies, I SMELLED SOMETHING. I SHOULD HAVE VERIFIED."
"You were forced to drag us here with you?", Tenuk threw while sliding down Thassalin's back. "And we left Retvik behind! We abandoned our big and strong fighter! How is he going to catch up to us?"
"He'll find a way," Nissy retorted. "Retvik is slow, but not stupid."
"Okay, but does Retvik know how to drive?"
Nissy blinked and turned back towards Tenuk. "Of course he knows how to drive."
"You've already seen Retvik driving a vehicle? He doesn't have a truck like you, and I've never seen him drive something like Kayel's little car, and if he started coming to work in a car, it's only because YOU drove us there. He just has a bike."
"A burst of laughter interrupted them. Thassalin suddenly burst out laughing and no one understood what was making him laugh. It took him a bit too long to regain his composure."
"I APOLOGIZE, BUT I IMAGINED YOUR BIG FRIEND IN ARMOR ON A MINISCULE CHILDREN'S BIKE PREVUED FOR TEMTHAN CHILDREN. IT WAS SO FUNNY! I WOULD HAVE WANTED TO BE GIFTED WITH TELEPATHY. IT'S A PRICELESS IDEA! ONE I CANNOT SHARE! "
Kayel chuckled, imagining what Thassalin was thinking. "Yes, it's just. But what have you gathered and why did you take flight so quickly?"
Thassalin growled, took to the skies and disappeared briefly, before returning and dropping a carcass in front of Nyssi. It was an Orothrack, a golden and white dragon-like creature, very rare. But it was missing its head. "ANOTHER DEATH. I HEAR THEIR SREAMS. I FEEL THEIR BLOOD. I AM PROGRAMMED TO PROTECT AND HUNT. AS YISINI DEMANDS. THE CREATURES ARE NEAR."
The powerful Thraki suddenly froze. Nyssi and Kayel also stopped, their attention drawn to a gap in the clearing. Something big and black was staring at them, hissing. Whatever it was, this thing opened two colossal pairs of wings and charged straight at Thassalin, not worrying about the three smaller beings in its path. Kayel and Tenuk managed to take cover just in time, but Nyssi was swept up and almost thrown onto Thassalin.
Thassalin reacted to the attack by grabbing Nissy and throwing her onto his back, using his extraordinary-length tail with incredible dexterity, before taking off. The black creature with two wings quickly gave chase.
Kayel puffed out air as he drew his gun from his back, then opened a pouch that had a clip of ammunition in it. He put it in his belt so he could access it easily, but soon realized that Nyssi, the Thraki, and the monster were no longer visible.
"Hey Tenuk, would you like to turn into something that can fly?", asked Kayel.
"Do you want to chase after them?"
"Yes, of course!"
"But... one of them is a giant monster!"
"And then? I have a super powerful rifle in my hands, ready to serve. I just need to see him to shoot him."
Tenuk hesitated, then backed off to give himself a little space. With a weak, slightly pained growl, his body unfolded, his fur was replaced by scales and his arms turned into wings. He quickly turned back into the normal clear blue Thraki, but his eyes remained red.
"Climb."
Tenuk had finally regained a more normal appearance of a Thraki, with his back covered in scales, but a pair of horns had also grown on top, making it practical for Kayel to hold on. Tenuk needed a bit of time to take off, but once in the air, he quickly oriented himself and attempted a pursuit.
However, Tenuk and Kayel quickly realized that they were not alone. A second dark creature emerged from below, and Tenuk barely managed to avoid it.
He supposed it was the other big frightening monster that was worrying Lanex? Kayel furrowed his brow as he tried to shoot the second beast, missed his target, and quickly reloaded his gun.
Tenuk didn't react. He was too focused on flying towards Nyssi and Thassalin, despite the other creature chasing after them. Kayel made a clumsy turn around himself, in order to face the monster. The fact that it was chasing them was a boon for Kayel, as it made it easier for him to aim and shoot. Two shots passed through the creature's upper wings, which let out a cry of pain as it disappeared under the trees again. Kayel didn't know if it was still following them, but it wouldn't be able to catch up to them.
Further on, Nyssi clung desperately, while Thassalin flew in a circle, firing blasts of flames at the dark monster. Although the creature was clearly wounded, it seemed furious and determined to fight on, and the fireballs seemed to have no effect. When Thassalin straightened up, Nyssi took advantage of the opportunity to draw her gun, a reliable one. It wasn't designed for this type of situation, but a burst of shots would surely be enough to at least dissuade the dark beast, wouldn't they?
